If this option is set to True the column names and types will be inferred from source data and DataFrame will be created with default options. If it is set to False (default), DataFrame schema will be specified based on source datastore definition.
The sample ratio of rows used for inferring
If schema inference is needed, SAMPLING_RATIO is used to determined the ratio of rows used for schema inference. The first row will be used if SAMPLING_RATIO is not set.

Specifies a string that indicates the date format to use when writing dates or timestamps. Custom date formats follow the formats at java.text.SimpleDateFormat. This applies to both DateType and TimestampType. If None is set, it uses the default value, yyyy-MM-dd. This option is only used when Storage Function is textFile or jsonFile.

Specifies a string that indicates the timestamp format to use when writing dates or timestamps. Custom date formats follow the formats at java.text.SimpleDateFormat. This applies to both DateType and TimestampType. If None is set, it uses the default value, yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.SSSXXX. This option is only used when Storage Function is textFile or jsonFile.
String representation of a null value.

Sets the string representation of a null value. If None is set, it uses the default value, empty string. Since 2.0.1, this nullValue param applies to all supported types including the string type. This option is only used when Storage Function is textFile.

This KM option allows adding custom store options. Any valid Spark option for the given format can be added here. Use the following syntax : '<option1>'='<value1>', '<option2>'='<value2>' ... These options will be appended to the list of principal store options.

COMPONENT NAME: LKM Spark to File COMPONENT VERSION: 1 AUTHOR: Oracle COMPATIBILITY: ODI 12.1.3.0.1 or above
DESCRIPTION This KM will store data into a file from a Spark Python variable and can be defined on the AP between the execution units, source technology Spark Python, target technology File.
The storage function to be used to load/store data

Choose one of storage functions to store data. "saveAsTextFile" is used to store the data into hdfs, a local file system or any Hadoop-supported file system URI. "saveAsJsonFile" is used to store the data in JSON format into hdfs, a local file system or any Hadoop-supported file system URI. "saveAsNewAPIHadoopFile" is used to store the data to a Hadoop file with an arbitrary new API InputFormat. "saveAsHadoopFile" is used to store data to a Hadoop file with an arbitrary InputFormat. "saveAsSequenceFile" is used to store data into key-value pairs.
When spark.useDataFrames is set to True, the data will be saved as RDD of JSON strings for saveAsNewAPIHadoopFile, saveAsHadoopFile, and saveAsSequenceFile.

Specify a fully qualified class name for writing the data.
Example: org.apache.hadoop.mapreduce.lib.input.TextOutputFormat (default) org.apache.hadoop.mapred.TextOutputFormat (saveAsHadoopFile)

Specify a fully qualified class for keys. Examples: org.apache.hadoop.io.NullWritable (default) org.apache.hadoop.io.Text
fully qualified classname of value Writable class

Specify a fully qualified class for values.
Examples: org.apache.hadoop.io.NullWritable org.apache.hadoop.io.Text (default)
